      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That feeling of total erasure is incredibly isolating, and it makes sense that you'd feel that way when the world seems to run on autopilot. It's easy to feel like a glitch in the system when everyone else is just checking boxes and scrolling feeds. But even if it feels like a \"deleted file\" right now, the reality is that you are the one who wrote the code for your own life. You have the power to rewrite it, even if it feels like you're stuck in a loop. You don't have to fix everything today, but you do deserve to feel seen, even if it's just by yourself.",
      "source": "target",
